snippet.textDisplay:
I genuinely want Ferrari to be competitive, because Mercedes hate to lose it'll drive them forwards. When Ferrari cheated this season with fuel flow, Mercedes prepared for another tight battle, then the Ferrari slowed down again and Mercedes are left way in front. I sincerely hope Ferrari are sandbagging, or it'll be down to Max and Max alone to keep the Mercedes on their toes.

Nobody wants to see a team winning by so much, but when you have the best people in a toxic culture like Ferrari, it compromises everything. Ferrari shot their own futures in the foot with their past dominance because they won by any means possible. Questionable tactics. It's showing now, they need to take a leaf out of Mercedes or even McLaren's book and improve their culture before they can hope to maintain a competitive edge with the best. They're going to be another Williams.
